sections.description:
**PCL** - Phishing Confidence Level (4-8: The message content is likely to be phishing.)
**BCL** - Bulk complaint level (4-7: The message is from a bulk sender that generates a mixed number of complaints. 8-9: The message is from a bulk sender that generates a high number of complaints.)
**SCL** - Spam confidence level (5-6: Spam filtering marked the message as Spam. 9: Spam filtering marked the message as High confidence spam)
`Note`: The default value is 0, but it can be changed when the "Process Microsoft's Email Headers" playbook runs.
sections.name: Microsoft Anti-Spam Headers
